# Full Orchestration Fix — Tenant Picker + Gap Remediation

## The Real-Life Scenario

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Admin as Tenant Admin
    participant Hub as Synapse Hub
    participant CRM as Salesforce/HubSpot/etc
    participant Ingest as /ingest/{tenant_id}
    participant GG as Graph Generator
    participant FS as Firestore
    participant CSM as CSM (Voice UI)
    participant Agent as AI Agent

    Note over Admin,Hub: Phase 1: Setup (one-time)
    Admin->>Hub: Create tenant + configure CRM
    Hub->>FS: Store config + webhook URL + secret
    Admin->>CRM: Paste webhook URL into CRM settings

    Note over CRM,FS: Phase 2: Webhook triggers (automatic)
    CRM->>Ingest: POST /ingest/{tenant_id} (deal closed)
    Ingest->>Ingest: HMAC verify + field mapping
    Ingest->>FS: Write deal summary (deals/{tid}/items/*)
    Ingest->>GG: Generate knowledge graph
    GG->>FS: Write skill_graphs/{tid}_{client}

    Note over CSM,Agent: Phase 3: Voice Briefing
    CSM->>Hub: Click "Launch Voice UI"
    Hub-->>CSM: Redirect to Voice UI ?tenant_id=X
    CSM->>CSM: Tenant Picker → Role Select → Dashboard
    CSM->>FS: GET deals (Firestore, tenant-scoped)
    CSM->>Agent: Start briefing session
    Agent->>FS: Read skill graph (tenant-scoped)
```

## Gaps Found

| # | Severity | Gap | Root Cause |
|---|----------|-----|-----------|
| 1 | 🔴 Critical | `client_id` mismatch | [ingest.py](file:///d:/rouca/DVM/workPlace/handoff/graph-generator/ingest.py) uses `"google"`, graph generator uses `"tid_google"` |
| 2 | 🔴 Critical | No tenant context in Voice UI | Landing → Roles → Dashboard drops `tenant_id` |
| 3 | 🟡 Major | RoleSelection CRM-coupled | Fetches `/api/crm/deals` without `tenant_id` |
| 4 | 🟡 Major | No Voice UI launch from Hub | Hub has no link to open Voice UI for a tenant |

## Proposed Changes

### Component 1: Voice UI — New Tenant Picker Page

#### [NEW] [TenantPicker.tsx](file:///d:/rouca/DVM/workPlace/handoff/frontend/src/components/TenantPicker.tsx)

A new page at `/tenants` that replaces the login screen for demo purposes.

- Fetches tenant list from the **Backend API** (new endpoint proxying Hub)
- Shows each tenant as a card with: name, brand, CRM type, integration status
- On click → navigates to `/roles?tenant_id={id}`
- In production this would be replaced by SSO/login

#### [MODIFY] [LandingPage.tsx](file:///d:/rouca/DVM/workPlace/handoff/frontend/src/components/LandingPage.tsx)
- CTA ("Get Started Free") → navigates to `/tenants` instead of `/roles`

#### [MODIFY] [App.tsx](file:///d:/rouca/DVM/workPlace/handoff/frontend/src/App.tsx)
- Add route: `/tenants` → `<TenantPicker />`

---

### Component 2: Tenant Context Propagation

#### [MODIFY] [RoleSelection.tsx](file:///d:/rouca/DVM/workPlace/handoff/frontend/src/components/RoleSelection.tsx)
- Read `tenant_id` from URL search params
- Fetch deals with `?tenant_id=X` for accurate deal counts
- Fetch tenant config from backend to get **enabled roles** for this tenant
- Navigate to `/dashboard?role=X&tenant_id=X` (preserving tenant context)

#### [MODIFY] [Dashboard.tsx](file:///d:/rouca/DVM/workPlace/handoff/frontend/src/components/Dashboard.tsx)
- Already reads `tenant_id` ✅ — no change needed

#### [MODIFY] [BriefingSession.tsx](file:///d:/rouca/DVM/workPlace/handoff/frontend/src/components/BriefingSession.tsx)
- Already reads `tenant_id` ✅ — no change needed

